job_description:
The Finance & Accounting Manager will be responsible for overseeing all aspects of the organization’s finances and accounting initiatives. The FAM will implement and analyze financial budget and forecasts, monitor treasury accounting functions, as well as stockbroking accounts & billings. The Finance & Accounting Manager will be responsible for maintaining adequate financial reporting in accordance with government regulations, legal compliance in Vietnam, and ensuring alignment with the group’s policies.
• Manage a financial accounting team for execution of key financial procedures (e.g. bookkeeping, assets management, prudential indicator reports, …), preparation of internal financial statements;
• Tax and audit activities including coordination with corporate functions;
• Preparation of budget and strategic planning, monitoring of business performance (key financials and performance indicators);
• Manage a treasury accounting team for documentation: payment orders, loan drawdown, loan payment, time deposit documents, and other documents;
• Monitor loan repayment and manage bank accounts, maintain sufficient balance for settlement;
• Ensure compliance with the Group and local policies & procedures.

requirements:
• University degree or higher in finance, auditing, accounting, business administration, or related fields;
• Qualified Accountant with 6+ years of experience working in finance, accounting and at least 3-5 years working experience in a similar position with a proven track record;
• Having chief accountant certificate, or ACCA, CPA certificates are advantages;
• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams at all levels;
• Strong organizational and leadership skills, with ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines;
• Strong literacy, for writing reports and presentations;
• Foreign language: Good command of spoken and written English;

 College or University (referred);
 At least 2 year experiences in similar fields or the audit field. Basic background of Quality Management System, preferably ISO9001:2000 Standard, Basic background of Compliance fields, EMS system, preferably the OHSAS 18001, SA8000 and ISO14001 system;
 Good knowledge of data analyses, strong problem solving skills and audit skills;
 High attention to detail and strong analytical skills;
 Good command of English, basic Mandarin communication is advantage;
 Able to work under high pressure, teamwork;
 Willing for business trips.

job_description:
We are looking for an HR & Admin Manager to oversee all aspect of human resources practices and processes with strong recruiting experience. As our HR manager, you will play a crucial role in driving our people strategy and ensuring the smooth operation of HR functions in the company. You will work closely with our leadership team to source, identify and onboard top talent while fostering a positive and inclusive working environment. This is an excellent opportunity for a motivated HR professional looking to make a significant impact on our organization’s growth.


• Responsible for the leadership and management of all functions of the Human Resource & Admin Department;
• Provide advices on HR policies and practices, people strategies and solutions and other employee related issues;
• Develop, update and implement HR policies and processes to ensure compliance with the group’s policies and local statutory and regulatory requirements;
• Manage and deliver full HR spectrum from manpower planning and budgeting; recruitment and selection, onboarding, employee engagement, talent management and succession planning, performance management as well as assessment of KPIs;
• Supervise the office administrative matter such as controlling and maintaining assets and inventories, managing office assets and expenditures, and ensuring that all administrative records are properly maintained.

requirements:
• University Degree or higher in Human Resource, Business Administration, or related fields;
• Having over 5 years of experience working in Human Resource Management, Labor Relation, Human Resource policy, and C&B;
• At least 3 years working experiences in a similar position with a proven track record;
• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams at all levels;
• Proficiency in labor law, personal income tax law, health insurance and social insurance law, and have good knowledge and skills in human resource management;
• Strong organizational and leadership skills, with ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines;
• Foreign language: Good command of spoken and written English;
• Candidate with experience at Securities, Banking, Fund Management Company is preferred.

